<title>UK: SOCCER-EUROPEAN CUP TRAINERS FACTFILE.</title>
<headline>SOCCER-EUROPEAN CUP TRAINERS FACTFILE.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ahead of next Wednesday's European</p>
<p>Cup final, the following are profiles of the careers of Juventus</p>
<p>coach Marcello Lippi and Borussia Dortmund trainer Ottmar</p>
<p>Hitzfeld.</p>
<p>MARCELLO LIPPI</p>
<p>Born: April 11, 1948</p>
<p>Playing career:</p>
<p>Boys' clubs San Paolino and Sant'Andrea in western city of</p>
<p>Viareggio. Then Stella Rossa (Red Star) Viareggio in 1962.</p>
<p>September 1964 - joined Sampdoria youth team</p>
<p>1969-70 - loaned to Serie C Savona</p>
<p>1970-1979 - Sampdoria, played as libero</p>
<p>1971 - called up for Italy under-23 team (two caps)</p>
<p>1979-81 - At serie B Pistoiese, then serie C Lucchese.</p>
<p>- - - -</p>
<p>Coaching career:</p>
<p>1982-85 - Sampdoria youth team</p>
<p>1985-86 - Pontedera (serie C2)</p>
<p>1986-87 - Siena (C1)</p>
<p>1987-88 - Pistoiese (C2)</p>
<p>1988-89 - Carrarese (C1)</p>
<p>1989-90 - Cesena (A)</p>
<p>    1991    - sacked after 17 games</p>
<p>1991-92 - Lucchese (B)</p>
<p>1992-93 - Atalanta (A)</p>
<p>1993-94 - Napoli (A)</p>
<p>    1994    - Appointed Juventus coach</p>
<p>- - - -</p>
<p>Major honours:</p>
<p>1994-95 - Italian league title, Italian Cup, UEFA Cup final</p>
<p>1995-96 - European Cup, Italian supercup</p>
<p>1996-97 - Intercontinental Cup. European Cup final. (Need</p>
<p>one point to clinch Italian league title).</p>
<p>OTTMAR HITZFELD</p>
<p>Born: Jan 12, 1949</p>
<p>Playing career:</p>
<p>TuS Stetten, FV Loerrach, Basel (Switzerland), VfB</p>
<p>Stuttgart, Lugano (Switzerland), Lucerne (Switzerland)</p>
<p>1972 Played for Germany in Munich Olympics</p>
<p>- - - -</p>
<p>Coaching career:</p>
<p>1983-84 - Zug (Switzerland)</p>
<p>1984-88 - Aarau (Switzerland)</p>
<p>1988-91 - Grasshoppers (Switzerland)</p>
<p>    1991    - Appointed Borussia Dortmund coach</p>
<p>- - - -</p>
<p>Major honours</p>
<p>1987-88 - Swiss Cup</p>
<p>1988-89 - Swiss Cup</p>
<p>1989-90 - Swiss league and Cup double</p>
<p>1990-91 - Swiss league title</p>
<p>1992-93 - UEFA Cup final</p>
<p>1994-95 - German league title</p>
<p>1995-96 - German league title</p>
<p>1996-97 - European Cup final</p>
</text>
